cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the vulnerability of neural networks to erroneous inputs and proposes a method to detect them using pre-trained neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the detection of adversarial attacks, which falls under the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of hidden and softmax feature vectors suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
